main event: An unidentified bright object was observed moving rapidly at a high altitude for 2-3 minutes before disappearing from sight.
interesting points: The object was sighted approximately 400 miles south of Minneapolis, Minnesota.
The sighting was reported by a local group and classified as a ground-visual observation.
Multiple aircraft, including a B-47 and a flight from Barksdale Air Force Base, reported sighting the unidentified object over Minneapolis.
The object was estimated to be flying at altitudes between 10,000 and 12,000 feet, and then later between 30,000 and 24,000 feet.
The radar sites in the vicinity of Minneapolis were unable to track any unidentified objects.
